MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/shells/pulse/components/chat/(ChatView|NarratorLine)\.tsx$
MATCH_CONTENT: (useNarratorLines|SOCIAL_INVITE|NarratorLine\b|channels\.filter|Object\.values\(channels|createdBy|memberIds\.length|factToTicker)
ADVISORY: |
  Pulse narrator lines are FACT-driven via TICKER.UPDATE — do NOT re-introduce
  channel-shape derivation.

  History: `useNarratorLines()` used to iterate `channels`, look at `type` /
  `createdBy` / `memberIds.length`, and emit lines ("Alice started talking to
  someone", "Alice and Bob started scheming", etc.). Retired 2026-04-14 when
  the ticker pipeline gained a SOCIAL_INVITE category.

  The current flow:
    Server: factToTicker handles DM_INVITE_SENT → SOCIAL_INVITE ticker
    Client: ChatView filters tickerMessages by category === SOCIAL_INVITE
            and renders them via <NarratorLine />

  DO NOT:
    - Re-introduce `useNarratorLines` or any channel-shape derivation of
      narrator content. Causes duplicate lines + stale data on reconnect.
    - Read `channels` to compute narrator text. Read `tickerMessages`.
    - Add narrator lines that name the TARGET of a DM/invite. Narrator lines
      are public intrigue — see memory/v1-narrator-intrigue.md. Copy decisions
      live server-side in `factToTicker`, not in the client renderer.

  DO:
    - Add new narrator subtypes by: (1) adding a fact type on the server,
      (2) handling it in `factToTicker` with a new TickerCategory, (3) filtering
      that category in ChatView and routing to NarratorLine with appropriate
      `kind` styling.
    - If you need to disambiguate within SOCIAL_INVITE, the TickerMessage.kind
      field carries a string discriminator ('initial' | 'add_member' today).

  Trade-off acknowledged: fact-driven narrator only fires for DMs/groups created
  AFTER the code lands. Pre-existing channels on live games don't backfill. If
  backfill becomes a requirement, extend tickerHistory replay on reconnect —
  don't re-add channel-shape derivation as a shortcut.
